The paper proposes a new approach to training neural models to exhibit transparency in a functional manner, which is a problem commonly studied in the machine learning community. The approach operates over structured data, which suggests that the paper may belong to sub-categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.CV (Computer Vision), and cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper specifically mentions deep graph and sequence models, which are commonly studied in the context of machine learning and artificial intelligence. Therefore, cs.LG and cs.AI are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also mentions chemical property prediction, temporal modeling, and molecule representation learning, which suggest that it may also belong to cs.DS, cs.CV, and cs.CL.
